Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is the vanishing gradient problem?
AI Response

In deep networks, gradients shrink exponentially during backpropagation, preventing early layers from
learning. Solutions include ReLU activations, residual connections, and LSTMs.

Example 1.2

User

What is an RNN?
AI Response

A Recurrent Neural Network processes sequential data with loops allowing information to persist. LSTMs and
GRUs are variants that address the vanishing gradient problem.

Example 1.3

User

What is deep learning?
AI Response

Deep learning is a subset of machine learning that uses multi-layered neural networks to learn
representations of data. It excels at tasks like image recognition, NLP, and speech synthesis.

Example 1.4

User

What is a neural network?
AI Response

A neural network is a series of algorithms modeled after the human brain, consisting of input, hidden, and
output layers, with weights adjusted during training to minimize prediction error.

Example 1.5

User

What is word embedding?
AI Response

Word embeddings map words to dense vectors where similar words are nearby. Word2Vec, GloVe, and
FastText are popular methods, used as NLP model input features.

Example 1.6

User

What is gradient descent?
AI Response

Gradient descent is an optimization algorithm that iteratively adjusts model parameters in the direction
opposite to the gradient of the loss function to find a minimum.

Example 1.7

User

What is precision vs recall?
AI Response



Precision is correct positive predictions / all positive predictions. Recall is correct positive predictions / all
actual positives. F1 score harmonically balances both.

Example 1.8

User

What is cross-validation?
AI Response

Cross-validation splits data into k folds, training on k-1 and validating on one, rotating until all folds serve as
validation. Results are averaged for robust performance estimation.

Example 1.9

User

What is the bias-variance tradeoff?
AI Response

High bias = underfitting (oversimplified model); high variance = overfitting (over-complex model). Good
models balance both to minimize total prediction error.

Example 1.10

User

What is a confusion matrix?
AI Response

A confusion matrix shows counts of true/false positives and negatives for a classifier, enabling computation of
accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score.



